{"kind":"article","variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/cambium\/gettingstarted"]}],"sections":[],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/documentation\/Cambium\/GettingStarted"},"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"metadata":{"title":"Getting Started","role":"article","modules":[{"name":"Cambium"}],"roleHeading":"Article"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/documentation\/Cambium"],["doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/documentation\/Cambium","doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/documentation\/Cambium\/CalculatorExample"]]},"abstract":[{"text":"Build your first Cambium tree by writing a tiny calculator parser.","type":"text"}],"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"text":"Overview","type":"heading","anchor":"Overview","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If you’re looking at Cambium, you’re probably writing a parser and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"considering using concrete syntax trees as its output. We’ll walk"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"through a complete example from defining a language all the way to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"walking the resulting tree."}]},{"type":"aside","style":"tip","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"This article is a narrative skim of Cambium’s API. For a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"hands-on, step-by-step build of a more substantial calculator with","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"precedence, error recovery, incremental reparse, witness-driven","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"analysis caches, parallel evaluation, and serialization — see","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/tutorials\/TableOfContents","isActive":true},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"name":"Tip"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"We’ll support addition and subtraction on integers, with parentheses"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"for grouping. The user is allowed to write nested expressions like"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"1-(2+5)"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The full pipeline:"}]},{"type":"orderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Define an enumeration of the kinds of tokens (like keywords) and","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"nodes (like “an expression”) that you want in your syntax, and","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"conform it to ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumCore\/SyntaxLanguage"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Create a ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumBuilder\/GreenTreeBuilder"},{"text":" and call ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumBuilder\/GreenTreeBuilder\/startNode(_:)"},{"text":",","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumBuilder\/GreenTreeBuilder\/token(_:text:)"},{"text":", and","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumBuilder\/GreenTreeBuilder\/finishNode()"},{"text":" from your parser.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Call ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumBuilder\/GreenTreeBuilder\/finish()"},{"text":" to obtain a ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumBuilder\/GreenBuildResult"},{"text":",","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"then call ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"result.snapshot.makeSyntaxTree()"},{"text":" to get a ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumCore\/SyntaxTree"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"you can traverse.","type":"text"}]}]}]},{"text":"Defining the language","type":"heading","anchor":"Defining-the-language","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"First, list the different parts of your grammar. We use a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"UInt32"},{"type":"text","text":"-backed"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"enum and let the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"@CambiumSyntaxKind"},{"type":"text","text":" macro derive every requirement"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"on "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumCore\/SyntaxKind"},{"type":"text","text":" for us. Operators and parentheses always render to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the same text, so we mark them with "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"@StaticText"},{"type":"text","text":"; integers vary"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"between occurrences and stay un-annotated."}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["import Cambium","import CambiumSyntaxMacros","","@CambiumSyntaxKind","enum CalcKind: UInt32, Sendable {","    \/\/ Tokens","    case integer = 1","    @StaticText(\"+\") case plus = 2","    @StaticText(\"-\") case minus = 3","    @StaticText(\"(\") case lparen = 4","    @StaticText(\")\") case rparen = 5","    @StaticText(\" \") case whitespace = 6","","    \/\/ Nodes","    case expr = 100","    case root = 101","","    \/\/ Sentinels for missing\/error recovery","    case missing = 200","    case error = 201","}"],"syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Next we tie the kind enum to a language type. Most of the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumCore\/SyntaxLanguage"},{"type":"text","text":" requirements have default implementations that work"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"for any "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumCore\/SyntaxKind"},{"type":"text","text":"-conforming enum, so the conformance is short:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["enum Calc: SyntaxLanguage {","    typealias Kind = CalcKind","","    static let rootKind: CalcKind = .root","    static let missingKind: CalcKind = .missing","    static let errorKind: CalcKind = .error","","    \/\/ Stable IDs in case we ever serialize trees.","    static let serializationID = \"com.example.calc\"","    static let serializationVersion: UInt32 = 1","","    \/\/ Trivia and node\/token classification.","    static func isTrivia(_ kind: CalcKind) -> Bool {","        kind == .whitespace","    }","","    static func isNode(_ kind: CalcKind) -> Bool {","        switch kind {","        case .expr, .root, .missing, .error:","            return true","        default:","            return false","        }","    }","","    static func isToken(_ kind: CalcKind) -> Bool {","        !isNode(kind)","    }","}"],"syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"That’s everything Cambium needs to specialize its generic types for our"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"language. Override "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumCore\/SyntaxLanguage\/isNode(_:)"},{"type":"text","text":" and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumCore\/SyntaxLanguage\/isToken(_:)"},{"type":"text","text":" when your language has dynamic-text token"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"kinds like "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"integer"},{"type":"text","text":"; the default classifier treats static-text kinds as"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"tokens and non-static kinds as nodes."}]},{"text":"Parsing into a green tree","type":"heading","anchor":"Parsing-into-a-green-tree","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For the purposes of this introduction, assume there is a lexer that"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"yields the following tokens:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["enum Token: Equatable {","    \/\/ Number strings are not yet parsed into actual numbers; we","    \/\/ remember the slice of the input that contains their digits.","    case integer(String)","    case plus","    case minus","    case lparen","    case rparen","    case eof","}"],"syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A simple "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Lexer"},{"type":"text","text":" over a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"String"},{"type":"text","text":" is part of the example flow but we"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"won’t show it inline; whatever lexer you have works fine as long as it"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"yields "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Token"},{"type":"text","text":"s in source order. To keep the parser short, these"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"snippets skip whitespace; a production CST parser should append trivia"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"tokens such as "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".whitespace"},{"type":"text","text":" to keep the tree fully lossless."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Let’s wire the lexer up to a parser"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"that owns a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumBuilder\/GreenTreeBuilder"},{"type":"text","text":":"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["struct Parser {","    private var lexer: Lexer","    private var builder: GreenTreeBuilder<Calc>","","    init(input: String) {","        self.lexer = Lexer(input: input)","        self.builder = GreenTreeBuilder<Calc>()","    }","}"],"syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In contrast to parsers that return abstract syntax trees, with Cambium"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the syntax tree nodes for every element of the language grammar have"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the same type: "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumCore\/GreenNode"},{"type":"text","text":" for the inner (“green”) tree and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumCore\/SyntaxNodeCursor"},{"type":"text","text":" (with optional "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumCore\/SyntaxNodeHandle"},{"type":"text","text":" projection)"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"for the outer (“red”) tree. Different kinds of nodes and tokens are"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"differentiated by their kind tag."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You can implement many types of parsers with Cambium. To get a feel for"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"how it works, consider a recursive-descent parser. With a more"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"traditional AST one would define different AST structs for each"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"syntactic category and have parsing functions return the matching AST"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"type. Because Cambium’s syntax trees are untyped, there is no explicit"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"AST representation that the parser would build. Instead, parsing into"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"a CST using the builder follows the source code more closely: you"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"tell Cambium about each new element you enter and every token the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"parser consumes."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The most trivial example is the root parser entry point, which just"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"opens a root node containing the whole expression and finishes it"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"again:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["extension Parser {","    mutating func parse() throws {","        builder.startNode(.root)","        try parseExpr()","        try builder.finishNode()","    }","}"],"syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"As there isn’t a static AST type to return, the parser is very"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"flexible as to what is part of a node. If the user is editing a struct"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and has not yet typed a field’s type, the CST node for the struct"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"doesn’t care that its child slot is empty. Similarly, leftover"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"identifiers from a half-deleted field can be a part of the struct"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"node without any modifications to the syntax tree definition. This"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"property is the key to why CSTs are such a good fit as a lossless"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"input representation, which necessitates the syntax tree to mirror the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"user-specific layout of whitespace and comments around the AST items."}]},{"text":"Speculative wrapping with checkpoints","type":"heading","anchor":"Speculative-wrapping-with-checkpoints","level":3},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In our calculator we have to deal with the fact that, when we see a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"number, the parser doesn’t yet know whether more operations follow."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"That is, in the expression "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"1 + 2"},{"type":"text","text":", the parser only knows it’s looking"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"at a binary operation once it sees the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"+"},{"type":"text","text":". The event-like model of"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"building trees in Cambium implies that when reaching the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"+"},{"type":"text","text":", the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"parser would already need to have entered a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CalcKind.expr"},{"type":"text","text":" node"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"for the whole input to be part of the expression."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To get around this, "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumBuilder\/GreenTreeBuilder"},{"type":"text","text":" provides"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumBuilder\/GreenTreeBuilder\/checkpoint()"},{"type":"text","text":", which we can call to “remember” the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"current builder position. Later, when the parser sees the following"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"+"},{"type":"text","text":", it can wrap everything since the checkpoint inside an"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CalcKind.expr"},{"type":"text","text":" node using"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumBuilder\/GreenTreeBuilder\/startNode(at:_:)"},{"type":"text","text":":"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["extension Parser {","    mutating func parseLhs() throws {","        switch try lexer.peek() {","        case .integer(let n):","            _ = try lexer.next()","            try builder.token(.integer, text: n)","","        case .lparen:","            \/\/ Wrap the grouped expression inside a node containing it","            \/\/ and its parentheses.","            builder.startNode(.expr)","            _ = try lexer.next()","            try builder.staticToken(.lparen)","            try parseExpr()","            guard case .rparen = try lexer.next() else {","                throw ParseError.missingRParen","            }","            try builder.staticToken(.rparen)","            try builder.finishNode()","","        case .eof:","            throw ParseError.unexpectedEOF","","        case let other:","            throw ParseError.unexpectedToken(other)","        }","    }","","    mutating func parseExpr() throws {","        \/\/ Remember our current position.","        let beforeExpr = builder.checkpoint()","","        \/\/ Parse the start of the expression.","        try parseLhs()","","        \/\/ Check whether the expression continues with `+ <more>` or","        \/\/ `- <more>`.","        let nextToken = try lexer.peek()","        let opKind: CalcKind","        switch nextToken {","        case .plus:  opKind = .plus","        case .minus: opKind = .minus","        case .rparen, .eof: return","        case let other:","            throw ParseError.unexpectedToken(other)","        }","","        \/\/ If so, retroactively wrap the (already parsed) LHS and the","        \/\/ following RHS inside an `expr` node.","        try builder.startNode(at: beforeExpr, .expr)","        _ = try lexer.next()","        try builder.staticToken(opKind)","        try parseExpr() \/\/ RHS","        try builder.finishNode()","    }","}"],"syntax":"swift"},{"text":"Static-text and dynamic-text tokens","type":"heading","anchor":"Static-text-and-dynamic-text-tokens","level":3},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Notice the split between"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumBuilder\/GreenTreeBuilder\/token(_:text:)"},{"type":"text","text":","},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumBuilder\/GreenTreeBuilder\/staticToken(_:)"},{"type":"text","text":", and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumBuilder\/GreenTreeBuilder\/missingToken(_:)"},{"type":"text","text":":"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumBuilder\/GreenTreeBuilder\/staticToken(_:)"},{"text":" only works on kinds whose","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumCore\/SyntaxLanguage\/staticText(for:)"},{"text":" returns non-","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"text":". The text comes","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"from the language definition; you don’t have to repeat it at the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"call site.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumBuilder\/GreenTreeBuilder\/token(_:text:)"},{"text":" only works on kinds with","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"no"}]},{"text":" static text — typically identifiers and literals. The supplied","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"string is interned in the builder’s ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumBuilder\/GreenNodeCache"},{"text":", so two","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"occurrences of the same identifier dedupe to one allocation.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumBuilder\/GreenTreeBuilder\/missingToken(_:)"},{"text":" records a parser-recovered","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"placeholder. It always renders to nothing.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumBuilder\/GreenTreeBuilder\/largeToken(_:text:)"},{"text":" is the right choice for","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"inherently unique payloads like long string literals, where","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"hash-interning would only waste hash work.","type":"text"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Mixing them up — for example, calling "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"token(.plus, text: \"+\")"},{"type":"text","text":" —"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"throws "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumBuilder\/GreenTreeBuilderError\/staticKindRequiresStaticToken(_:)"},{"type":"text","text":" so"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"schema mistakes are caught at the call site instead of producing a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"silently malformed tree."}]},{"text":"Obtaining the parser result","type":"heading","anchor":"Obtaining-the-parser-result","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Our parser can now parse our little arithmetic language, but its"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"methods don’t return anything. Where does the syntax tree come from?"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"The answer is "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumBuilder\/GreenTreeBuilder\/finish()"},{"type":"text","text":", which finally consumes"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the builder and returns a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumBuilder\/GreenBuildResult"},{"type":"text","text":":"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["extension Parser {","    consuming func finish() throws -> GreenBuildResult<Calc> {","        try builder.finish()","    }","}"],"syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The result includes the green "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumBuilder\/GreenBuildResult\/root"},{"type":"text","text":", the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumBuilder\/GreenBuildResult\/resolver"},{"type":"text","text":" (sealed once at "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"finish()"},{"type":"text","text":" via the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"interner’s "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumCore\/TokenInterner\/makeResolver()"},{"type":"text","text":"), and the underlying"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumBuilder\/GreenTreeContext"},{"type":"text","text":" (accessible via"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumBuilder\/GreenBuildResult\/intoContext()"},{"type":"text","text":"). The context bundles the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"interner with the cache as a namespace-bound unit; pass it to the next"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"builder via "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumBuilder\/GreenTreeBuilder\/init(context:)"},{"type":"text","text":" to keep"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"token-key namespace identity stable across reparses."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To work with the syntax tree, materialize a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumCore\/SyntaxTree"},{"type":"text","text":" from the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"build result’s "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumBuilder\/GreenBuildResult\/snapshot"},{"type":"text","text":":"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["let input = \"11+2-(5+4)\"","var parser = Parser(input: input)","try parser.parse()","","let result = try parser.finish()","let tree = result.snapshot.makeSyntaxTree()"],"syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"tree"},{"type":"text","text":" is a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"~Copyable"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumCore\/SyntaxTree"},{"type":"text","text":". To traverse it, hand a closure"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumCore\/SyntaxTree\/withRoot(_:)"},{"type":"text","text":"; the closure receives a borrowed"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumCore\/SyntaxNodeCursor"},{"type":"text","text":" on the root."}]},{"text":"Traversing the tree","type":"heading","anchor":"Traversing-the-tree","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The cursor API mirrors how you’d write a recursive-descent walker, but"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"without the per-node allocations. Borrow-on-demand instead of"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"return [Cursor]"},{"type":"text","text":":"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["tree.withRoot { root in","    print(\"root kind: \\(Calc.name(for: root.kind))\")","    print(\"root range: \\(root.textRange)\")","","    root.forEachChild { child in","        print(\" child: \\(Calc.name(for: child.kind)) \\(child.textRange)\")","    }","}"],"syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For a depth-first walk over every descendant:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["tree.withRoot { root in","    _ = root.visitPreorder { node in","        \/\/ Return .skipChildren or .stop to control descent.","        print(\"\\(Calc.name(for: node.kind)) \\(node.textRange)\")","        return .continue","    }","}"],"syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For a token-aware walk (most editor scenarios), use"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumCore\/SyntaxNodeCursor\/walkPreorderWithTokens(_:)"},{"type":"text","text":" or"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumCore\/SyntaxNodeCursor\/tokens(in:_:)"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"text":"Reading text without allocating","type":"heading","anchor":"Reading-text-without-allocating","level":3},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Materializing source text as "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"String"},{"type":"text","text":" is occasionally what you want"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"("},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumCore\/SyntaxNodeCursor\/makeString()"},{"type":"text","text":"), but for hot-path scans prefer the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"borrowed text view:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["tree.withRoot { root in","    root.withText { text in","        if text.contains(0x2B) { \/\/ '+'","            \/\/ ...","        }","    }","}"],"syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumCore\/SyntaxText"},{"type":"text","text":" walks the green tree on demand and yields chunks"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"straight from the resolver’s interned bytes — no copies, no"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"allocations unless you ask for a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"String"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"text":"Promoting to a copyable, Sendable tree","type":"heading","anchor":"Promoting-to-a-copyable-Sendable-tree","level":3},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SyntaxTree"},{"type":"text","text":" is "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"~Copyable"},{"type":"text","text":" so traversal stays unambiguous about"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"ownership. When you need to publish a tree to SwiftUI, hand it to a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Task"},{"type":"text","text":", or store it in a long-lived snapshot, promote it to a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumCore\/SharedSyntaxTree"},{"type":"text","text":":"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["let shared = tree.intoShared()","","\/\/ Sendable across actors, retained until the last reference is gone.","await Task.detached {","    shared.withRoot { root in","        \/\/ ... background work","    }","}.value"],"syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For long-lived references to "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"specific nodes","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":", use"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumCore\/SharedSyntaxTree\/rootHandle()"},{"type":"text","text":" and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumCore\/SyntaxNodeCursor\/makeHandle()"},{"type":"text","text":" to obtain copyable"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumCore\/SyntaxNodeHandle"},{"type":"text","text":" values that you can store in dictionaries,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"attach diagnostics to, or send across actors."}]},{"text":"Editing a tree","type":"heading","anchor":"Editing-a-tree","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Trees are persistent. To “edit” one, call"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SharedSyntaxTree.replacing(_:with:context:)"},{"type":"text","text":" with the handle of the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"node to replace and a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumCore\/ResolvedGreenNode"},{"type":"text","text":" (or"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumBuilder\/GreenTreeSnapshot"},{"type":"text","text":", or "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumBuilder\/GreenBuildResult"},{"type":"text","text":")"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"of the replacement. The result is a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumCore\/ReplacementResult"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"with the new tree and a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumCore\/ReplacementWitness"},{"type":"text","text":" describing"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the structural change. The "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"context:"},{"type":"text","text":" argument is a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumBuilder\/GreenTreeContext"},{"type":"text","text":" whose interner shares the target"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"tree’s namespace — pass "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"result.intoContext()"},{"type":"text","text":" from the build that"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"produced the target tree to keep namespace identity intact."}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["let original = tree.intoShared()","","\/\/ Build a replacement subtree, reusing the original's context so the","\/\/ replacement's keys land in the same namespace.","var rebuilder = GreenTreeBuilder<Calc>(context: result.intoContext())","rebuilder.startNode(.expr)","try rebuilder.token(.integer, text: \"42\")","try rebuilder.finishNode()","let replacement = try rebuilder.finish()","let replacementSnapshot = replacement.snapshot","","\/\/ Decide which node to replace — for example, the root's first child.","let target: SyntaxNodeHandle<Calc> = original.withRoot { root in","    root.withFirstChild { $0.makeHandle() }!","}","","var context = replacement.intoContext()","let edit = try original.replacing(target, with: replacementSnapshot, context: &context)","let witness = edit.witness","let next = edit.intoTree()"],"syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Inspect "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"witness"},{"type":"text","text":" to translate any v0 references (handles you"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"held before the edit) into v1: "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"witness.classify(path:)"},{"type":"text","text":" returns a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumCore\/ReplacementOutcome"},{"type":"text","text":" telling you whether the path is unchanged, an"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"ancestor of the edit, the replaced node itself, or a descendant of"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the deleted region."}]},{"text":"Incremental parsing","type":"heading","anchor":"Incremental-parsing","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For an editor that reparses on every keystroke, you don’t want to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"discard the entire tree each time. The CambiumIncremental module"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"provides:"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumIncremental\/ParseInput"},{"text":" — the bundle of ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"(textUTF8, edits, previousTree)"},{"text":" your","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"parser receives for each parse pass.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumIncremental\/IncrementalParseSession"},{"text":" — long-lived state that aggregates","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"reuse counters and an accepted-reuse log across parses.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumIncremental\/ReuseOracle"},{"text":" — the parser-facing interface that offers candidate","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"subtrees from the previous tree at given offsets.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumIncremental\/ParseWitness"},{"text":" — the post-parse summary: which subtrees were","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"carried over by reference, which regions were freshly parsed.","type":"text"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A typical reparse loop:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["let session = IncrementalParseSession<Calc>()","var sharedTree: SharedSyntaxTree<Calc>? = nil","","\/\/ On each edit:","let input = ParseInput<Calc>(text: newText, edits: edits, previousTree: sharedTree)","let oracle = session.makeReuseOracle(for: input)","","\/\/ Inside your parser, before parsing a node of kind .expr at an old-tree","\/\/ offset that survived edit invalidation:","let accepted = try oracle.withReusableNode(startingAt: oldExprStart, kind: .expr) { reusable in","    \/\/ Capture the witness data before the borrowed cursor leaves scope.","    let oldPath = reusable.childIndexPath()","    let green = reusable.green { $0 }","","    \/\/ Splice the reused subtree into the new tree without re-parsing it.","    try builder.reuseSubtree(reusable)","","    \/\/ The parser\/integrator owns new-path bookkeeping because it knows","    \/\/ where this node is being appended in the output tree.","    return Reuse(green: green, oldPath: oldPath, newPath: newExprPath)","}","","if let accepted {","    session.recordAcceptedReuse(","        oldPath: accepted.oldPath,","        newPath: accepted.newPath,","        green: accepted.green","    )","}","","let result = try builder.finish()","sharedTree = result.snapshot.makeSyntaxTree().intoShared()","","let witness = ParseWitness(","    oldRoot: input.previousTree?.rootGreen,","    newRoot: result.root,","    reusedSubtrees: session.consumeAcceptedReuses()",")"],"syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The witness is the right anchor for higher-layer identity tracking:"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"diagnostics, selections, fold state, anything attached to nodes by"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"identity. Cambium does not maintain those mappings itself — it"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"provides the structural primitive and lets you compose the policy"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"appropriate for your editor."}]},{"text":"Analysis sidecars","type":"heading","anchor":"Analysis-sidecars","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"CambiumAnalysis provides two per-node sidecar shapes. Use"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumAnalysis\/SyntaxMetadataStore"},{"type":"text","text":" for multi-typed annotations during a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"single analysis pass, and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumAnalysis\/ExternalAnalysisCache"},{"type":"text","text":" for one"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"long-lived, single-typed memoization cache that can bulk-evict old tree"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"versions."}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["let metadata = SyntaxMetadataStore<Calc>()","let typeKey = SyntaxDataKey<String>(\"com.example.calc.value-kind\")","metadata.set(\"integer\", for: typeKey, on: exprHandle)","","let values = ExternalAnalysisCache<Calc, Int64>()","let key = AnalysisCacheKey(","    identity: exprHandle.identity,","    namespace: \"com.example.calc.eval\"",")","values.set(42, for: key)","values.removeValues(notMatching: latestTree.treeID)"],"syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Both stores key nodes by "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumCore\/SyntaxNodeIdentity"},{"type":"text","text":". If you want cached"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"values to survive an incremental reparse, consume "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumIncremental\/ParseWitness"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"records before evicting: translate entries whose old paths fall inside reused"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"subtrees onto the corresponding new paths, then call"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumAnalysis\/ExternalAnalysisCache\/removeValues(notMatching:)"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SyntaxDataKey"},{"type":"text","text":" equality is based on its string name, not its "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Value"},{"type":"text","text":" type; use"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"namespaced strings so unrelated passes do not accidentally share the same slot."}]},{"text":"AST Layer","type":"heading","anchor":"AST-Layer","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"While Cambium is built for concrete syntax trees, applications often"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"want to work with either a CST or an AST representation, or freely"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"switch between them. The CambiumASTSupport module gives you the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"minimal vocabulary to do this: define one "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumASTSupport\/TypedSyntaxNode"},{"type":"text","text":"-conforming"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"type per AST kind, then use "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumCore\/SyntaxNodeHandle\/asTyped(_:)"},{"type":"text","text":" and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumCore\/SyntaxNodeCursor\/withTyped(_:_:)"},{"type":"text","text":" to safely down-cast generic"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"nodes."}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["enum ExprNode: TypedSyntaxNode {","    typealias Lang = Calc","    static let rawKind = Calc.rawKind(for: .expr)","}","","if let exprHandle = nodeHandle.asTyped(ExprNode.self) {","    exprHandle.withCursor { exprCursor in","        \/\/ ... statically known to be an expr","    }","}"],"syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"A grammar-specific layer (likely generated by tooling) is the right","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"place to define one spec type per kind, with kind-specific accessors","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"built on top. Cambium does not ship grammar generators in core — the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumASTSupport\/TypedSyntaxNode"},{"text":" protocol is the contract that an AST overlay","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"should target.","type":"text"}]},{"text":"License","type":"heading","anchor":"License","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Cambium is distributed under the same dual MIT \/ Apache-2.0 license as","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the upstream ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"cstree"},{"text":" it draws inspiration from.","type":"text"}]}],"kind":"content"}],"references":{"doc://org.cambium.Cambium/documentation/Cambium/CalculatorExample":{"kind":"article","role":"sampleCode","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/documentation\/Cambium\/CalculatorExample","type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A complete end-to-end example using Cambium to parse, traverse, edit,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and evaluate a small arithmetic language."}],"title":"Calculator","url":"\/documentation\/cambium\/calculatorexample"},"doc://org.cambium.Cambium/documentation/Cambium":{"url":"\/documentation\/cambium","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/documentation\/Cambium","type":"topic","abstract":[{"text":"A Swift-native concrete syntax tree library inspired by Rust’s","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/domenicquirl\/cstree","isActive":true},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"title":"Cambium","kind":"symbol","role":"collection"},"doc://org.cambium.Cambium/tutorials/TableOfContents":{"kind":"overview","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/tutorials\/TableOfContents","abstract":[{"text":"Cambium is a Swift-native concrete syntax tree library. This","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"tutorial series walks you through building a small but","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"production-shaped calculator language end-to-end: a recursive-","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"descent parser that produces a lossless tree, a typed AST overlay,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"an evaluator with memoized analysis, persistent edits with","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"identity-preserving witnesses, an incremental reparse loop, fork-","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"join evaluation across structured-concurrent tasks, parallel","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"parsing with externalized interning, and on-disk serialization.","type":"text"}],"url":"\/tutorials\/tableofcontents","title":"Build a Calculator with Cambium","role":"overview"},"https://github.com/domenicquirl/cstree":{"url":"https:\/\/github.com\/domenicquirl\/cstree","type":"link","identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/domenicquirl\/cstree","titleInlineContent":[{"code":"cstree","type":"codeVoice"}],"title":"cstree"}}}